-- Shanghai Futures Exchange to Increase Margins, Trading Limits, CBN Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-25T07:59:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-25/shanghai-futures-exchange-to-increase-margins-trading-limits-cbn-reports.html
The Shanghai Futures Exchange will
raise trading margins and daily price move limits for contracts
including copper, rubber, aluminum, gold, fuel oil and steel,
the Chinese Business News today reported citing a notice from
the exchange.  The bourse will lift the margin on trades of copper,
aluminum, steel wire, gold and fuel oil to 10 percent and to 12
percent for reinforced bar steel and zinc contracts, the report
said. Rubber contract margins will rise to 13 percent, it said.
The measaure will start from Nov. 30.  Additionally, the daily price move limits for all the
contracts will be increased to 6 percent, the report said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
